FBIS4-35539 "drnes106bb_94002" FBIS-NES-94-106 Daily Report 1 Jun 1994 Inter-Arab Affairs Arab Group Applies for Security Council Seat Arab Group Applies for Security Council Seat NC0106131494 Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network in Arabic 1130 GMT 1 Jun 94 NC0106131494 Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network Arabic BFN [Text] Ambassador Nabil al-'Arabi, Egypt's permanent delegate to the United Nations, has stated that an Arab group has submitted an official application to obtain a permanent seat at the UN Security Council. In a statement made today on the sidelines of the Non-Aligned Movement Conference, al-'Arabi said that the African group has also requested two permanent seats on the council. He explained that the UN General Assembly is expected to consider the expansion of the UN Security Council membership and including other countries at its session next year.
